text: Gianina-Elena Beleagă (born 21 May 1995) is a Romanian rower. She is twice world champion in the women's lightweight double sculls event winning back to back titles in 2017 and 2018 for Romania. She competed in the women's lightweight double sculls event at the 2016 Summer Olympics. ==References== ==External links== * * Category:1995 births Category:Living people Category:Romanian female rowers Category:Olympic rowers of Romania Category:Rowers at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:World Rowing Championships medalists for Romania
